---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Pool Builders City of Gold Coast | Full LGA Coverage | (03) 9003 0108"
  description="Swimming pool construction and resurfacing across the City of Gold Coast LGA — beachside, canal-estate, hinterland and northern Gold Coast. New concrete, fibreglass, full resurface. QBCC-licensed.">
  <Fragment slot="head">
    <link rel="canonical" href="https://goldcoastpoolbuilders.com.au/city-of-gold-coast/">
  </Fragment>

  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-inner">
      <span class="hero-eyebrow">City of Gold Coast LGA &middot; full coverage</span>
      <h1>Pool builders &amp; resurfacers across the <span class="accent">City of Gold Coast</span>.</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        From Coolangatta in the south to Coomera in the north, beachside through to
        the hinterland, canal estates included. One LGA, one council jurisdiction,
        four pool-construction contexts &mdash; we work all of them weekly.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="tel:+61390030108">&#9742; Call (03) 9003 0108</a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Book a free on-site quote</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <span class="section-eyebrow">Full coverage</span>
      <h2>Suburbs we cover.</h2>
      <div class="divider"></div>
      <div style="max-width: 65rem;">
        <h3>Featured suburb pages.</h3>
        <p>Each with real local context &mdash; pool stock age, typical block, our recommended approach.</p>
        <div class="areas-grid" style="margin: 1.5rem 0 2.5rem 0;">
          <a class="area-pill" href="/mermaid-beach/">Mermaid Beach</a>
          <a class="area-pill" href="/burleigh-heads/">Burleigh Heads</a>
          <a class="area-pill" href="/mudgeeraba/">Mudgeeraba</a>
          <a class="area-pill" href="/robina/">Robina</a>
          <a class="area-pill" href="/helensvale/">Helensvale</a>
        </div>

        <h3>Other Gold Coast suburbs.</h3>
        <div class="areas-grid" style="margin: 1.5rem 0 2.5rem 0;">
          <a class="area-pill" href="#">Surfers Paradise</a>
          <a class="area-pill" href="#">Broadbeach</a>
          <a class="area-pill" href="#">Palm Beach</a>
          <a class="area-pill" href="#">Currumbin</a>
          <a class="area-pill" href="#">Tugun</a>
          <a class="area-pill" href="#">Coolangatta</a>
          <a class="area-pill" href="#">Bilinga</a>
          <a class="area-pill" href="#">Miami</a>
          <a class="area-pill" href="#">Nobby Beach</a>
          <a class="area-pill" href="#">Sanctuary Cove</a>
          <a class="area-pill" href="#">Sovereign Islands</a>
          <a class="area-pill" href="#">Paradise Point</a>
          <a class="area-pill" href="#">Hope Island</a>
          <a class="area-pill" href="#">Runaway Bay</a>
          <a class="area-pill" href="#">Biggera Waters</a>
          <a class="area-pill" href="#">Tallai</a>
          <a class="area-pill" href="#">Tamborine Mountain</a>
          <a class="area-pill" href="#">Carrara</a>
          <a class="area-pill" href="#">Nerang</a>
          <a class="area-pill" href="#">Pacific Pines</a>
          <a class="area-pill" href="#">Oxenford</a>
          <a class="area-pill" href="#">Coomera</a>
          <a class="area-pill" href="#">Pimpama</a>
          <a class="area-pill" href="#">Ormeau</a>
        </div>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Four zones, four design conversations.</h3>
        <p>
          <strong>Beachside zone</strong> (Mermaid Beach, Burleigh Heads, Palm Beach,
          Currumbin, Coolangatta, Miami, Nobby Beach): narrow 500&ndash;750m&sup2;
          blocks, original 1970s&ndash;1990s pool stock now in the resurface window.
          Side-access constraint usually means small fibreglass or compact concrete
          rectangular; ageing pebble interiors need quartz or full-tile redo.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>Canal-estate zone</strong> (Sanctuary Cove, Sovereign Islands,
          Paradise Point, Hope Island, Runaway Bay, Broadbeach Waters): high-spec
          waterfront blocks, freeform concrete with infinity edge or sun-deck, glass
          fencing to maintain canal view, premium tile finishes. Mandatory pool-side
          tidal-zone setback under City of Gold Coast canal-corridor rules &mdash;
          we&rsquo;ve been doing these since 2018.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>Hinterland zone</strong> (Mudgeeraba, Tallai, Tamborine, Worongary,
          Maudsland): acreage 1,000m&sup2;&ndash;5ha+ blocks on granite-based hinterland
          soil. Freeform concrete pools, often with large surrounding deck or pavilion.
          Bushfire BAL ratings apply to surrounding decking/cabana but the pool
          structure itself isn&rsquo;t BAL-rated.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>Northern growth-corridor zone</strong> (Robina, Helensvale, Hope
          Island land-side, Coomera, Pimpama, Ormeau): newer 2000s+ master-planned
          estates, mix of new fibreglass installs and existing 1990s&ndash;2000s pools
          entering their first resurface window. Family-led design.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Pool stock age &mdash; where the work is in 2026.</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>1970s pools (pre-AS 1839):</strong> Most have been replaced once. Surviving ones often have hand-built construction details that need careful structural assessment. Bring in a builder, not a resurfacer.</li>
          <li><strong>1980s pools (original Gold Coast suburban wave):</strong> Have already been resurfaced once. Now on 2nd or 3rd resurface, or considering rebuild. Equipment is fully end-of-life.</li>
          <li><strong>1990s pools (peak Gold Coast build wave):</strong> RIGHT IN THE RESURFACE WINDOW. Original pebble surfaces are scrapy and chemically tired. About 35% of our 2026 work is 1990s pebble&rarr;quartz or pebble&rarr;tile re-interior.</li>
          <li><strong>2000s pools:</strong> Entering 1st resurface window. Salt-chlorinator equipment is in 2nd or 3rd replacement cycle.</li>
          <li><strong>2010s pools:</strong> Still in good shape. Equipment lifecycle starting to hit (pumps and chlorinator cells).</li>
          <li><strong>2020s+ new builds:</strong> Mostly fibreglass shells in new northern estates; concrete for canal blocks and architectural acreage.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">QBCC + planning &mdash; single-LGA simplicity.</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>QBCC licence:</strong> Required for all pool construction, resurfacing and substantial renovation in QLD. We hold Class 1 Builder + swimming pool contractor endorsement.</li>
          <li><strong>Form 17:</strong> Compliance certificate lodged with private building certifier. Standard pools self-assess (no planning DA needed).</li>
          <li><strong>Form 23:</strong> Pool Safety Certificate from registered Pool Safety Inspector before final approval. 5-year renewal cycle for sale/lease.</li>
          <li><strong>Single council:</strong> City of Gold Coast is the only LGA across the whole region &mdash; one set of rules, one fee schedule, one inspection regime. Unlike Brisbane (BCC + 4 surrounds) or Sydney (40+ LGAs).</li>
          <li><strong>Canal-corridor approvals:</strong> Sanctuary Cove, Hope Island and Sovereign Islands canal-frontage pools need a tidal-zone setback check + sometimes a Maritime Safety Queensland sign-off if structure encroaches over high-water mark. We coordinate.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

